\title{Omero Integration}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Microscopy data management platform. Access images via Python, retrieve datasets, analyze pixels, manage ROIs/annotations, batch processing, for high-content screening and microscopy workflows."}

\subtree{
\title{OMERO Integration}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{OMERO is an open-source platform for managing, visualizing, and analyzing microscopy images and metadata. Access images via Python API, retrieve datasets, analyze pixels, manage ROIs and annotations, for high-content screening and microscopy workflows.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when:}

\ul{
\li{Working with OMERO Python API (omero-py) to access microscopy data}
\li{Retrieving images, datasets, projects, or screening data programmatically}
\li{Analyzing pixel data and creating derived images}
\li{Creating or managing ROIs (regions of interest) on microscopy images}
\li{Adding annotations, tags, or metadata to OMERO objects}
\li{Storing measurement results in OMERO tables}
\li{Creating server-side scripts for batch processing}
\li{Performing high-content screening analysis}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\p{This skill covers eight major capability areas. Each is documented in detail in the references/ directory:}

\subtree{
\title{1. Connection & Session Management}
\p{\strong{File}: \code{\startverb references/connection.md\stopverb}}

\p{Establish secure connections to OMERO servers, manage sessions, handle authentication, and work with group contexts. Use this for initial setup and connection patterns.}

\p{\strong{Common scenarios:}}

\ul{
\li{Connect to OMERO server with credentials}
\li{Use existing session IDs}
\li{Switch between group contexts}
\li{Manage connection lifecycle with context managers}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Data Access & Retrieval}
\p{\strong{File}: \code{\startverb references/data_access.md\stopverb}}

\p{Navigate OMERO's hierarchical data structure (Projects → Datasets → Images) and screening data (Screens → Plates → Wells). Retrieve objects, query by attributes, and access metadata.}

\p{\strong{Common scenarios:}}

\ul{
\li{List all projects and datasets for a user}
\li{Retrieve images by ID or dataset}
\li{Access screening plate data}
\li{Query objects with filters}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Metadata & Annotations}
\p{\strong{File}: \code{\startverb references/metadata.md\stopverb}}

\p{Create and manage annotations including tags, key-value pairs, file attachments, and comments. Link annotations to images, datasets, or other objects.}

\p{\strong{Common scenarios:}}

\ul{
\li{Add tags to images}
\li{Attach analysis results as files}
\li{Create custom key-value metadata}
\li{Query annotations by namespace}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Image Processing & Rendering}
\p{\strong{File}: \code{\startverb references/image_processing.md\stopverb}}

\p{Access raw pixel data as NumPy arrays, manipulate rendering settings, create derived images, and manage physical dimensions.}

\p{\strong{Common scenarios:}}

\ul{
\li{Extract pixel data for computational analysis}
\li{Generate thumbnail images}
\li{Create maximum intensity projections}
\li{Modify channel rendering settings}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Regions of Interest (ROIs)}
\p{\strong{File}: \code{\startverb references/rois.md\stopverb}}

\p{Create, retrieve, and analyze ROIs with various shapes (rectangles, ellipses, polygons, masks, points, lines). Extract intensity statistics from ROI regions.}

\p{\strong{Common scenarios:}}

\ul{
\li{Draw rectangular ROIs on images}
\li{Create polygon masks for segmentation}
\li{Analyze pixel intensities within ROIs}
\li{Export ROI coordinates}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. OMERO Tables}
\p{\strong{File}: \code{\startverb references/tables.md\stopverb}}

\p{Store and query structured tabular data associated with OMERO objects. Useful for analysis results, measurements, and metadata.}

\p{\strong{Common scenarios:}}

\ul{
\li{Store quantitative measurements for images}
\li{Create tables with multiple column types}
\li{Query table data with conditions}
\li{Link tables to specific images or datasets}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{7. Scripts & Batch Operations}
\p{\strong{File}: \code{\startverb references/scripts.md\stopverb}}

\p{Create OMERO.scripts that run server-side for batch processing, automated workflows, and integration with OMERO clients.}

\p{\strong{Common scenarios:}}

\ul{
\li{Process multiple images in batch}
\li{Create automated analysis pipelines}
\li{Generate summary statistics across datasets}
\li{Export data in custom formats}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{8. Advanced Features}
\p{\strong{File}: \code{\startverb references/advanced.md\stopverb}}

\p{Covers permissions, filesets, cross-group queries, delete operations, and other advanced functionality.}

\p{\strong{Common scenarios:}}

\ul{
\li{Handle group permissions}
\li{Access original imported files}
\li{Perform cross-group queries}
\li{Delete objects with callbacks}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Installation}
\pre{\startverb
uv pip install omero-py
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Requirements:}}

\ul{
\li{Python 3.7+}
\li{Zeroc Ice 3.6+}
\li{Access to an OMERO server (host, port, credentials)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start}
\p{Basic connection pattern:}

\pre{\startverb
from omero.gateway import BlitzGateway

# Connect to OMERO server
conn = BlitzGateway(username, password, host=host, port=port)
connected = conn.connect()

if connected:
    # Perform operations
    for project in conn.listProjects():
        print(project.getName())

    # Always close connection
    conn.close()
else:
    print("Connection failed")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Recommended pattern with context manager:}}

\pre{\startverb
from omero.gateway import BlitzGateway

with BlitzGateway(username, password, host=host, port=port) as conn:
    # Connection automatically managed
    for project in conn.listProjects():
        print(project.getName())
    # Automatically closed on exit
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Selecting the Right Capability}
\p{\strong{For data exploration:}}

\ul{
\li{Start with \code{\startverb references/connection.md\stopverb} to establish connection}
\li{Use \code{\startverb references/data_access.md\stopverb} to navigate hierarchy}
\li{Check \code{\startverb references/metadata.md\stopverb} for annotation details}
}

\p{\strong{For image analysis:}}

\ul{
\li{Use \code{\startverb references/image_processing.md\stopverb} for pixel data access}
\li{Use \code{\startverb references/rois.md\stopverb} for region-based analysis}
\li{Use \code{\startverb references/tables.md\stopverb} to store results}
}

\p{\strong{For automation:}}

\ul{
\li{Use \code{\startverb references/scripts.md\stopverb} for server-side processing}
\li{Use \code{\startverb references/data_access.md\stopverb} for batch data retrieval}
}

\p{\strong{For advanced operations:}}

\ul{
\li{Use \code{\startverb references/advanced.md\stopverb} for permissions and deletion}
\li{Check \code{\startverb references/connection.md\stopverb} for cross-group queries}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Workflows}
\subtree{
\title{Workflow 1: Retrieve and Analyze Images}
\ol{
\li{Connect to OMERO server (\code{\startverb references/connection.md\stopverb})}
\li{Navigate to dataset (\code{\startverb references/data_access.md\stopverb})}
\li{Retrieve images from dataset (\code{\startverb references/data_access.md\stopverb})}
\li{Access pixel data as NumPy array (\code{\startverb references/image_processing.md\stopverb})}
\li{Perform analysis}
\li{Store results as table or file annotation (\code{\startverb references/tables.md\stopverb} or \code{\startverb references/metadata.md\stopverb})}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow 2: Batch ROI Analysis}
\ol{
\li{Connect to OMERO server}
\li{Retrieve images with existing ROIs (\code{\startverb references/rois.md\stopverb})}
\li{For each image, get ROI shapes}
\li{Extract pixel intensities within ROIs (\code{\startverb references/rois.md\stopverb})}
\li{Store measurements in OMERO table (\code{\startverb references/tables.md\stopverb})}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow 3: Create Analysis Script}
\ol{
\li{Design analysis workflow}
\li{Use OMERO.scripts framework (\code{\startverb references/scripts.md\stopverb})}
\li{Access data through script parameters}
\li{Process images in batch}
\li{Generate outputs (new images, tables, files)}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Error Handling}
\p{Always wrap OMERO operations in try-except blocks and ensure connections are properly closed:}

\pre{\startverb
from omero.gateway import BlitzGateway
import traceback

try:
    conn = BlitzGateway(username, password, host=host, port=port)
    if not conn.connect():
        raise Exception("Connection failed")

    # Perform operations

except Exception as e:
    print(f"Error: {e}")
    traceback.print_exc()
finally:
    if conn:
        conn.close()
\stopverb}
}

